## Primitive.Resolve type

Converts type `T` to a `Primitive.Type`<!-- -->.

**Signature:**

```typescript
type Resolve<T> = T extends Name ? Resolve<Map[T]> : T extends Type ? NonNullable<Mutable<T>> : never;
```
**References:** [Name](./toolkit.primitive.name.md)<!-- -->, [Resolve](./toolkit.primitive.resolve.md)<!-- -->, [Map](./toolkit.primitive.map.md)<!-- -->, [Type](./toolkit.primitive.type.md)<!-- -->, [Mutable](./toolkit.mutable.md)

## Example


```ts
type A = Primitive.Resolve<"string">; // string
type B = Primitive.Resolve<string>; // string
```
